crime= 'DRUG/NARCOTIC'
Weekdate = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']

fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(20, 8))

df_crime = df[df["Category"] == crime]
count_year = {yr: 0 for yr in Weekdate}
for yr in Weekdate:
    df_week = df_crime[df_crime["DayOfWeek"].str.contains(yr)]
    for j in ['23','24','1', '2']:
        count_year[yr] += len(df_week[df_week["Time"].str.split(":").str[0].astype(int) == int(j)])
ax[0].bar(count_year.keys(), count_year.values())
ax[0].set_title("N. of "+ crime +" per week-day")
ax[0].set_xlabel('Day of week')
ax[0].set_ylabel("Crime count")

count_year = {}
for j in range(0,25):
    count_year[j] = len(df_crime[df_crime["Time"].str.split(":").str[0].astype(int) == j])
ax[1].bar(count_year.keys(), count_year.values())
ax[1].set_title("N. of "+ crime +" per month by category")
ax[1].set_xticks(range(0, 24, 1))
ax[1].set_xlabel('Daytime')
ax[1].set_ylabel("Crime count")

plt.show()

# Defined x-axis ticks for month plot
Month = ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'June', 'July', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec']

# Convert the 'Date' column to datetime
df_crime['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df_crime['Date'])

# Extract day, month, and year
df_crime['Day'] = df_crime['Date'].dt.day
df_crime['Month'] = df_crime['Date'].dt.month
df_crime['Year'] = df_crime['Date'].dt.year

# Group by day, month, and year and count incidents
daily_counts = df_crime.groupby(['Year', 'Month', 'Day']).size().reset_index(name='Incidents')

# Draw a table showing the occurrence happening in different weekday and month
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))
weekday_order = list(calendar.day_name)
daily_counts['DayOfWeek'] = pd.Categorical(pd.to_datetime(daily_counts[['Year', 'Month', 'Day']]).dt.day_name(), categories=weekday_order, ordered=True)
calendar_data = daily_counts.pivot_table(index='DayOfWeek', columns='Month', values='Incidents', aggfunc='sum', fill_value=0)
sns.heatmap(calendar_data, cmap='YlGnBu', linewidths=0.5, linecolor='black', annot=True, fmt='g', cbar=False)

# Set axes label and the title and slightly adjust xtick places
plt.title(crime +' Incidents by Weekday and Month',size=15)
plt.xticks(ticks=np.arange(1, 13) - 0.5, labels=Month)
plt.xlabel('Month',size=15)
plt.ylabel('Day of Week',size=15)

plt.show()

focuscrimes = set(['WEAPON LAWS', 'PROSTITUTION', 'DRIVING UNDER THE INFLUENCE', 'ROBBERY', 'BURGLARY', 'ASSAULT', 'DRUNKENNESS', 'DRUG/NARCOTIC', 'TRESPASS', 'LARCENY/THEFT', 'VANDALISM', 'VEHICLE THEFT', 'STOLEN PROPERTY', 'DISORDERLY CONDUCT'])
df['DateTime'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'] + ' ' + df['Time'])
df['HourOfWeek'] = df['DateTime'].dt.dayofweek * 24 + df['DateTime'].dt.hour

hourly_counts = df.groupby(['Category', 'HourOfWeek']).size().reset_index(name="counts")
In [51]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(13, figsize=(20,100))

# Get unique values of "HourOfWeek" without using unique()
unique_hours = sorted(hourly_counts['HourOfWeek'].unique())

# Assign a color to each unique hour
colors = plt.cm.plasma(np.linspace(0, 1, len(unique_hours)))  # Adjust the colormap as needed

R_dict ={}
i = 0
for c1 in focuscrimes:
    if c1 != crime:
        
        x = hourly_counts[hourly_counts["Category"] == crime]["counts"]
        y = hourly_counts[hourly_counts["Category"] == c1]["counts"]
        x = np.array(x).reshape(-1, 1)
        y = np.array(y).reshape(-1, 1)
        
        mx = np.mean(x)
        my = np.mean(y)
        mxsq = np.sum(x**2)
        mxy = np.sum(x*y)
        N = len(x)
        a = (mxy - N * mx * my)/(mxsq - N * mx * mx)
        b = np.mean(y - a * x)
        
        reg = LinearRegression().fit(x,y)
        yline = a * x + b
        R = 1- np.sum(np.square(y-yline))/np.sum(np.square(y-my))

        R_dict[c1+ " " +crime] = R
        ax[i].plot(x, yline, color='red')
        annotation = f'y = {a:.2f}x + {b:.2f}\n$R^2$ = {R:.4f}'
        ax[i].annotate(annotation, xy=(0.05, 0.85), xycoords='axes fraction', fontsize=12)
        
        for idx, hour in enumerate(unique_hours):
            x = hourly_counts[(hourly_counts["Category"] == crime) & (hourly_counts["HourOfWeek"] == hour)]["counts"].values.reshape(-1, 1)
            y = hourly_counts[(hourly_counts["Category"] == c1) & (hourly_counts["HourOfWeek"] == hour)]["counts"].values.reshape(-1, 1)

            # Plot data points for each hour with a unique color
            ax[i].scatter(x,y, color=colors[idx])
        ax[i].set_ylabel(crime,size=20)
        ax[i].set_xlabel(c1,size=20)


        i += 1
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
